# Minimal API Migration Conventions

Use this rule to keep migrations to ASP.NET Core Minimal API safe and consistent.

## Project layout and dependencies

- `Core` project: models, DTOs, helpers, service interfaces only.
- `Infrastructure` project: services, adapters, and DI registration.
- `Api` project: host and endpoint mapping.
- `Tests` project: unit + integration + contract coverage.

Allowed references: `Api -> Infrastructure -> Core`, `Api -> Core`, `Tests -> all`.

## Endpoints

- Preserve existing routes and response contracts.
- Keep endpoint handlers thin and map routes through extension methods.
- Register literal routes before parameterized routes.

## Constraints

- Keep business logic in services.
- Do not commit secrets.
- Comments in English.
